which she endured grievous <notvariant>torturings</notvariant>; and<lb/>
yet to enable her to speak such things, surely<lb/>
so extraordinary a Teacher requires more<lb/>
then ordinary attention. When <notvariant>Jonah</notvariant>, who<lb/>
had <normalised orig="bin" auto="false">been</normalised> so close a student in the Whales belly<lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <fw type="pageNum" n="136">L4</fw>
                  <pb n="12"/>
                  <lb/>
<normalised orig="Colledge" auto="true">College</normalised>, came to preach to the <notvariant>Ninevites</notvariant><lb/>
the <normalised orig="strangenesse" auto="true">strangeness</normalised> of the Relation concerning<lb/>
the Preacher, might make his Sermons take<lb/>
more with them, <quote type="biblical" ana="Mt 12.41">Shall not they rise in Judgement<lb/>
against the men of this Generation?</quote> some<lb/>
it may be (with Pharaohs <normalised orig="South-sayers" auto="false">Soothsayers</normalised>) will<lb/>
acknowledge the finger of God is in this, when<lb/>
his whole hand is visible: but if men <normalised orig="sleight" auto="true">slight</normalised><lb/>
such dispensations, no wonder: for <quote type="biblical" ana="Lk 16.31">if they<lb/>
